{
  "texts": [
    "Remarkably, the N-grams model exhibited superior performance on the PHEME and CAT datasets compared to the LSTM DL model presented by Ajao et al. (2018) for fake tweet detection.",
    "Applying the DL approach to the PHEME dataset, the N-grams-based model surpassed LSTM by 48% in F-measure and 2% in accuracy.",
    "This emphasizes the effectiveness of relying primarily on text features for optimal performance.",
    "The advantage of N-gram features lies in their ease of extraction from textual content.",
    "In addition to eliminating the need for extensive data corpora during the training process, as required by handcrafted features such as word embeddings, the exceptional performance of N-gram features stems from their ability to discern words and phrases effectively, enabling the model to grasp contextual information surrounding each word."
  ]
}